          "reviewRating": {
            "@type": "Rating",
            "ratingValue": "1",
            "bestRating": "5",
            "worstRating": "1"
          },
          "reviewBody": "The most pathetic, irresponsible staff I have ever seen in my life.\n1. A day before any event, they inform parents to make arrangements for props that are needed in events.\nTeachers give lame excuses like technical glitches in telegram group or handsets rather than accepting their fault.\n2. Vacations are extended/school timings are changed without informing well in advance without keeping in mind - how working parents would manage.\n3. Annual function is planned when whole city is waterlogged. Despite parents reached to attend annual day taking early leaves from their jobs/businesses. & at school, they are seated in classrooms to watch annual show at the zoom link. Despite the fact that school has community centre in close proximity which can be booked considering weather condition but why management will bother about parents and spend money to book community centre or any other place. Irony is, principal said to cooperate rather accepting mistake for all the mismanagement.\n90% of the parents couldn't even see their kids on stage due to bad forecast quality by school.\n4. Kids are asked to bring balloons, stars and other decoratives to decorate school at christmas. School despite taking huge fees, asking kids to bring decorative.\n5. List is long....... beware of such school and spoiling foundation years of your kids by enrolling in such schools.",
          "publisher": {
            "@type": "Organization",
            "name": "Yellow Slate"
          }
        },
